{
  "texts": [
    "Data entry consists of two parts, one is helping users to create the table structure, and the other is the precise entry of data by converting unstructured data formats into (semi-) structured tables.",
    "When creating a table, LLMs can help list the possible column headers.",
    "For instance, Google Sheets offers a feature that generates a new table with suggested column headers and example table data.",
    "Another application scenario involves converting tables from images or PDFs into formats natively suited for tables, facilitating subsequent stages of table processing.",
    "This feature requires AI systems capable of multimodal table understanding [13,46], and systems like ChatGPT-4o can now convert table images into structured formats."
  ]
}